(40, 9, 11, 40, 11, 19, 19, NULL, 'Connection of Jesus and Sinners', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' association with publicans and sinners, highlighting the criticism he faced for this behavior. The first passage shows the Pharisees questioning his actions, while the second passage reflects on the accusations made against him, reinforcing the theme of his acceptance of those marginalized by society.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
