(40, 9, 11, 46, 5, 9, 11, NULL, 'Eating with Sinners and Fornicators', 'This connection highlights the theme of association with those deemed sinful. Both passages address the implications of eating with individuals labeled as sinners or fornicators, emphasizing the need for discernment in such relationships.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 11, 48, 2, 15, 15, 'sinners', 'Connection of Sinners and Gentiles', 'Both passages emphasize the distinction between Jews and those labeled as sinners. In Matthew, the Pharisees question why Jesus associates with publicans and sinners, while Galatians refers to Gentiles as sinners, highlighting a perceived separation.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 11, 58, 5, 2, 2, 'publicans and sinners', 'Compassion for Sinners', 'This connection highlights the theme of compassion towards those considered outcasts or sinful. Both passages emphasize the importance of understanding and empathizing with the ''ignorant'' and ''sinners''.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
