(40, 9, 13, 42, 19, 10, 10, 'I will have mercy, and not sacrifice', 'Mercy and Salvation Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of seeking and saving those who are lost, emphasizing mercy over sacrifice. Both passages reflect the mission of Jesus to reach out to sinners and offer them repentance and salvation.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 13, 54, 1, 13, 16, 'I will have mercy, and not sacrifice', 'Mercy and Sinners Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of mercy extended to sinners. Matthew highlights God''s desire for mercy over sacrifice, while 1 Timothy illustrates Paul''s experience of receiving mercy as a chief sinner. This connection highlights the transformative power of grace for those who repent.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
